See Also
Shigellosis - Costa Rica 20010727.1472
Date: Sat, 28 Jul 2001 07:50:01 +0300
From: "Stephen A. Berger, M.D." <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON <http://www.GideonOnline.com>

In fact, official government reports suggest that shigellosis is not
common[ly reported in Costa Rica:
192 cases were reported in 1992;
49 in 1993;
2 in 1994;
74 in 1995;
73 in 1996;
40 in 1997;
45 in 1998;
38 in 1999;
89 in 2000.
Rates per 100,000:
2.2 in 1995;
2.1 in 1996;
1.1 in 1997;
1.2 in 1998;
2.26 in 1999.
